  <description type="morphology">Stems commonly branched. Leaf base narrower to little wider than the limb. Sexual condition dioicous, autoicous or synoicous, occasionally polyoicous. Seta usually 1.5–2.5 cm. Capsule with theca reaching 3–4 mm, operculum commonly 1–1.5 mm, peristome distinctly twisted.</description>
